<subSubSection pageId="31" pageNumber="110" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authority="Hamilton, 1822" authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1822" box="[151,491,186,212]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gutum">
<emphasis box="[151,308,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Gobius gutum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hamilton, F." box="[314,491,186,212]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" refId="ref27364" refString="Hamilton, F. (1822) An Account of the Fishes Found in the River Ganges and its Branches. Archibald Constable, Edinburgh, 405 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. title. 59540" type="book" year="1822">Hamilton, 1822</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, from 
<collectingCountry box="[562,620,186,212]" name="India" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">India</collectingCountry>
has been considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Hamilton, 1822)" baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[1083,1306,186,212]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="giuris">
<emphasis box="[1083,1306,186,212]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Glossogobius giuris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Kottelat, M." pageId="31" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 663" refId="ref27999" refString="Kottelat, M. (2013) The fishes of the inland waters of southeast Asia: a catalogue and core bibliography of the fishes known to occur in freshwaters, mangroves and estuaries. Raffles Bulletin of Zoology, Supplement 27, 1 - 663." type="journal article" year="2013">Kottelat (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. However, the original description, clearly indicates that the upper jaw overhangs the lower jaw, unlike 
<taxonomicName authority="Gill, 1859" box="[198,350,258,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[198,350,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Glossogobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Hora, S. L." box="[365,504,258,285]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" pagination="169 - 192" refId="ref27922" refString="Hora, S. L. (1929). An aid to the study of Hamilton Buchanan's &quot; Gangetic Fishes &quot;. Memoirs of the Indian Museum, 9, 169 - 192." type="journal article" year="1929">Hora (1929)</bibRefCitation>
published Hamilton’s original drawing of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hamilton" authorityYear="1822" box="[986,1145,258,284]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gutum">
<emphasis box="[986,1145,258,284]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Gobius gutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and it is clearly a species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1837" box="[229,316,295,321]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Awaous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[229,316,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Awaous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Britz, R." box="[331,470,294,320]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" pagination="1 - 641" refId="ref26795" refString="Britz, R. (2019). Francis Hamilton's Gangetic Fishes in colour. Ray Society Monographs, 181, 1 - 641, 228 pls." type="journal article" year="2019">Britz (2019)</bibRefCitation>
provided the image in colour and added the 
<typeStatus box="[979,1027,295,321]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">type</typeStatus>
locality as Podma River. 
<bibRefCitation author="Plamoottil, M." pageId="31" pageNumber="110" pagination="12 - 23" refId="ref28538" refString="Plamoottil, M. (2016) Systematic Accounts on Percoid Fishes of Manimala River of Travancore. International Journal of Research in Environmental Science, 2 (5), 12 - 23. https: // doi. org / 10.20431 / 2454 - 9444.0205002" type="journal article" year="2016">Plamoottil (2016)</bibRefCitation>
recorded and figured the species as 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Hamilton" baseAuthorityYear="1822" box="[679,843,331,357]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Awaous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gutum">
<emphasis box="[679,843,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Awaous gutum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="31.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">
<taxonomicName authority="Jerdon, 1949" authorityName="Jerdon" authorityYear="1949" box="[151,498,366,392]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[151,345,366,392]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Gobius neglectus</emphasis>
Jerdon, 1949
</taxonomicName>
. Although not treated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Koumans, F. P." box="[780,968,366,393]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" refId="ref28072" refString="Koumans, F. P. (1953) The Fishes of the Indo-Australian Archipelago. Gobioidea. Vol. 10. Brill, Leiden, 423 pp." type="book" year="1953">Koumans (1953)</bibRefCitation>
the species was originally compared with species of 
<taxonomicName authority="Gill, 1859" box="[314,466,402,428]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[314,466,402,428]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Glossogobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The species was described as having a sloping snout and an eye going into head length 5 times. The counts are given as D 6 I,11 and anal I,10 or 11. Under 
<taxonomicName authority="Jerdon (1849)" authorityName="Jerdon" authorityYear="1849" box="[962,1284,438,464]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="kokius">
<emphasis box="[962,1121,438,464]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Gobius kokius</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Jerdon, T. C." box="[1128,1284,438,464]" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" pagination="139 - 149" refId="ref27957" refString="Jerdon, T. C. (1849) On the fresh water fishes of southern India. Madras Journal of Literature and Science, 15 (Pt 1), 34 (Art. 2), 139 - 149." type="journal article" year="1849">Jerdon (1849)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
describes the snout as being in line with the back and D I,9 anal I,8. That species is consistent with the “giuris” head form, but 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jerdon" authorityYear="1949" box="[240,346,510,536]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Gobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="neglectus">
<emphasis box="[240,346,510,536]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">neglectus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a closer match to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Valenciennes" authorityYear="1837" box="[575,662,511,537]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Awaous" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[575,662,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Awaous</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, although it is reported from near the mountain and may belong elsewhere, but is clearly not a 
<taxonomicName authority="Gill, 1859" box="[494,646,546,572]" class="Actinopterygii" family="Gobiidae" genus="Glossogobius" kingdom="Animalia" order="Perciformes" pageId="31" pageNumber="110" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[494,646,546,572]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="110">Glossogobius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
